<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="351" type="collection and habitat data">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Collection and habitat data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="351">
This species is associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus" order="Pinales" pageId="2" pageNumber="351" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Pinus</taxonomicName>
spp., and larvae occur in galls on twigs (
<bibRefCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="351">Anderson and Kissinger 2002</bibRefCitation>
). In New Brunswick, adults were captured during July and August in Lindgren funnel traps deployed in an old red pine forest and an old mixed forest with red pine. One specimen was reared from red pine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
